## 7. 📁 Project Structure Explained

```
url-shortner/
├── src/
│   ├── server.js          Entry point — starts the app, graceful shutdown
│   ├── app.js             Express app setup, middleware chain, route mounting
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── env.js         Load & validate all env variables
│   │   ├── database.js    Knex DB connection instance (singleton)
│   │   └── redis.js       ioredis instance + BullMQ connection factory
│   ├── routes/            Route definitions + Swagger JSDoc comments
│   ├── controllers/       HTTP request/response handlers (thin layer)
│   ├── services/          Business logic (thick layer, most code here)
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   ├── auth.js        JWT authenticate + optionalAuth
│   │   ├── rateLimiter.js Token bucket rate limiter (Redis + Lua)
│   │   ├── validator.js   Request body validation middleware
│   │   └── errorHandler.js Central error handler + AppError class
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── snowflake.js   Snowflake ID generator (64-bit unique IDs)
│   │   ├── base62.js      Base62 encoder/decoder
│   │   ├── blacklist.js   Domain blacklist (Redis Set)
│   │   └── urlValidator.js URL safety validation
│   ├── workers/
│   │   └── analyticsWorker.js BullMQ worker for async analytics
│   └── db/migrations/     Knex migration files (versioned DB schema)
├── public/                Frontend (static HTML/CSS/JS, served by Express)
│   ├── index.html         Landing page
│   ├── dashboard.html     User dashboard
│   ├── login.html / signup.html / pricing.html / password.html
│   └── js/ css/
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml     Local dev: PostgreSQL + Redis
├── knexfile.js            Knex DB config (dev + prod)
└── package.json
```

**Architecture Pattern: Layered (MVC + Service Layer)**
- Routes → define endpoints, apply middleware chain
- Controllers → handle HTTP, call services, send responses
- Services → all business logic, DB queries, cache operations
- Utils → pure utility functions (no side effects)
- Middleware → cross-cutting concerns

