## 8. 🔑 Key Design Decisions & Why

### 8.1 Snowflake ID Generator
Twitter-inspired 64-bit unique ID:
```
[1 bit sign][41 bits timestamp][10 bits machineId][12 bits sequence]
```
- Custom Epoch: 2026-01-01 → fits in 41 bits for ~69 years
- **Why?** Globally unique without DB coordination. Works across distributed nodes.
- **4096 IDs/ms** per machine without collision.
- **Machine ID:** Configurable via `MACHINE_ID` env var.

### 8.2 Base62 Encoding
- Charset: `0-9 a-z A-Z` (62 chars)
- A 64-bit Snowflake ID → 6-8 character Base62 string
- URL-safe (no `+`, `/`, `=` like Base64)
- 62^5 = ~916 million possible 5-char codes

### 8.3 Cache Strategy
- **Write-through cache:** On URL creation, immediately cached in Redis
- **Cache invalidation:** On URL update/delete, Redis key deleted
- **TTL:** 1 hour (3600 seconds)
- **Key pattern:** `url:<shortCode>`

### 8.4 One-Time Links — 301 vs 302
- One-time → 302 (temporary), prevents browser caching
- Permanent → 301 (permanent), browser caches, offloads server

### 8.5 Fail-Open vs Fail-Closed
- Rate limiter: **Fail-Open** (if Redis down, allow requests) — availability > strict limiting
- Auth middleware: **Fail-Closed** (if JWT invalid, reject) — security > availability

### 8.6 Anonymous vs Authenticated Shortening
- Anonymous users CAN create links (no account needed)
- `user_id` in `urls` table is nullable
- This is a growth strategy: let anonymous users try → convert to paid

---

## 9. 🌐 Frontend & Route Order

The frontend is static HTML served by Express. Route order in `app.js` is critical:

```javascript
// 1. Static assets (/public) - CSS, JS files
app.use(express.static('public'));

// 2. API routes (/api/...) - most specific
app.use('/api/auth', authRoutes);
app.use('/api', urlRoutes);

// 3. Named pages (/dashboard, /login, etc.)
['dashboard','login','signup','pricing'].forEach(page => {
  app.get(`/${page}`, sendFile(`${page}.html`));
});

// 4. Short code redirect wildcard — MUST be last
app.get('/:shortCode([a-zA-Z0-9_-]{3,30})', redirectHandler);

// 5. 404 → serve index.html (SPA-like fallback)
```

**Why this order matters:** If wildcard was first, `/dashboard` would be treated as a short code lookup!

